=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_Crackle_ex1 ===

DESCRIPTION: A bright pure_tone sound, with complex oscillator character around 1903 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: bright
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 1902.7314
  harmonic_decay_rate: -0.6512
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5985
  pitch_clarity: 0.0000
  inharmonicity: 0.0239
  type: complex
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -9.0225
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: Crackle Example 1
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/Crackle.html
// Tags: Crackle, Classes, noise
// ---
// --- Example 1 ---
{ Crackle.ar(1.95, 0.5) }.play;

// modulate chaos parameter
{ Crackle.ar(Line.kr(1.0, 2.0, 3), 0.5, 0.5) }.play;
